perl-Tcl
------------------------------------------
The Tcl extension provides a small but complete interface into libtcl 
and any other Tcl-based library. It lets you create Tcl interpreters (as 
perl5 objects), bind in commands to them (either perl subroutines or C 
functions dynamically loaded with the DynaLoader extension) and execute 
Tcl code in those interpreters.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  perl-5.10.0-3
  tcl-8.4.16-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.9-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1

Canonical website:
  http://search.cpan.org/dist/Tcl/

Canonical download:
  http://search.cpan.org/CPAN/authors/id/V/VK/VKON/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack perl-Tcl-0.95-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./perl-Tcl-0.95-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/perl-Tcl-0.95-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/perl-Tcl-0.95-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.10/i686-cygwin/Tcl.pm
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.10/i686-cygwin/auto/Tcl/.packlist
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.10/i686-cygwin/auto/Tcl/Tcl.dll
  /usr/share/doc/perl-Tcl-0.95/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/perl-Tcl-0.95/Changes
  /usr/share/doc/perl-Tcl-0.95/README
  /usr/share/man/man3/Tcl.3pm.gz

------------------

